<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9DEF5EFF12F9CEFDE4F966" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF12F9CEFF5EF901" blockId="53.[151,1437,1658,1902]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF12F9CEFE86F92D" bold="true" box="[151,307,1659,1685]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9DEF5EFEB8F9CEFE04F92D" box="[317,433,1659,1685]" name="Argentina" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Argentina</collectingCountry>
: Misiones; 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9DEF5EFDB2F9CEFD3BF92D" box="[567,654,1659,1685]" name="Bolivia" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
: La Paz; 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9DEF5EFD78F9CEFCF3F92D" box="[765,838,1659,1685]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFCD6F9CFFC1FF92D" bold="true" box="[851,938,1658,1685]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9DEF5EFCD6F9CFFC1FF92D" box="[851,938,1658,1685]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Paraná</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
, 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9DEF5EFC3EF9CEFB2DF92D" box="[955,1176,1659,1685]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9DEF5EFB22F9CEFAABF92D" box="[1191,1310,1659,1685]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
; 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9DEF5EFAA9F9C9FA2CF92E" box="[1324,1433,1660,1686]" name="Paraguay" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9DEF5EFF12F92AFF52F901" box="[151,231,1695,1721]" country="Paraguay" name="Guaira" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Guairá</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42F976FDE4F966" blockId="53.[151,1437,1658,1902]" box="[199,593,1730,1758]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42F976FDFFF965" bold="true" box="[199,586,1730,1757]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
New record for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9DEF5EFE2AF977FDFFF965" box="[431,586,1730,1757]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9DEF5EFF42F952FDFBF8D5" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42F952FC23F8F1" blockId="53.[151,1437,1658,1902]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42F952FEE7F8B9" bold="true" box="[199,338,1767,1793]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Comments:</emphasis>
Despite this is a new record for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9DEF5EFD65F952FCDBF8B9" box="[736,878,1767,1793]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, the species was already recorded in neighbouring areas both in 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9DEF5EFEB4F8BEFEC0F89D" box="[305,373,1803,1829]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and in 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9DEF5EFE49F8BEFD8AF89D" box="[460,575,1803,1829]" name="Argentina" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. Differently from the other species of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9DEF5EFC76F8BEFB30F89D" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1011,1157,1803,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Steirodontini">Steirodontini</taxonomicName>
previously presented, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9DEF5EFA02F8B9FE97F8F1" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Stilpnochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginoides">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFA02F8B9FE97F8F1" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">S. marginoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be more restricted to southern South America.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9DEF5EFF42F8E6FDFBF8D5" blockId="53.[151,1437,1658,1902]" box="[199,590,1875,1902]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9DEF5EFF42F8E6FED1F8D5" bold="true" box="[199,356,1875,1901]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Bioacoustics:</emphasis>
Sound not recorded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
